Response ID: resp_1104
Response Text: Fund Black native creative Austinites - who at this point seem to be nonexistent, wiped out, &-or hidden/buried in displacement due to being undercapitalized for so long, and creatives who are not from here absorbing all the resources. There should be some type of consistent/non-negotiable funding for Black natives of this land who are the bedrock of the city & have the most historical knowledge & lived experience of the city. The funds should be enough to cover general operational support at the least (which is oxygen for a dying breed that continues to fight to stay in Austin). There's just no honor/dignity, and most creative natives feel like outsiders now because they are far, few & overlooked. I've seen 2nd, 3rd, 4th & 5th generation Austinites scrap for dollars while people who just got here or have only been here a few years cash in! Let's start with respecting our own first & go from there.

